race.description: Irresistible Pools And Spas Mdn Plate
race.comment: A big Waller contingent with ARTGIRL (4) the pick of them. Debuted 13 days ago over 1100m at Wyong and showed great determination to go under narrowly in a small field. Should enjoy the extra 100m and with a nice trail from this gate can finish over the top. Gary Portelli's JAEGERS (8) looks the best chance to upset the Waller army. Followed the leader into the straight but just failed in the same race as ARTGIRL at Wyong when facing the starter for the first time. Doubt there will be much between them again. SNITZEL MISS (14) is the class runner back from a 37-week spell. Has raced twice and filled minor placings in the Widden and Sweet Embrace. Will get back from the wide gate but can storm home and win without surprising. Debutante WEEKEND MARKET (2) won a recent trial by eight lengths which not many do. Watch the betting. Zoustar filly PLAINTIFF (11) won a recent Randwick trial in good fashion - has a lot to live up to after costing $2.2 million as a yearling.
